Functions Held in Czech Republic and Iran 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- A film show was held at the Taekwon-do Club of the "Kyebaek Self-Defence Art " in the Czech Republic, a briefing on the situation on the Korean Peninsula and a film show were held by the Red Crescent Relief and Rescue Organization of Iran on Nov. 13 and 18 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 88th birth anniversary of Anti-Japanese War Hero Kim Jong Suk.
 The participants of the film shows watched Korean films including the "Grand Gymnastic and Artistic Performance 'Arirang', 'Kim Il Sung Prize' Winner", "Old Home in Mt. Paektu Shining with Glory" and "Korea, Land of Morning Calm." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the above-said functions said that the DPRK has solved its strategic problems including the nuclear issue in its interests, steadfastly standing in confrontation with the U.S., adding that this is entirely thanks to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching Kim Jong Il possessed of inexhaustible energy and brilliant wisdom, we were convinced of the rosy future of the DPRK, they stressed.

Adoption of Anti-North "Resolution on Human Rights Performance" Assailed by South Koreans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- There is mounting criticism of the adoption of the anti-north "resolution on human rights performance" at the UN General Assembly.
 Jong Un Sik, representative of the Peace Net of south Korea, in a statement released on Nov. 18 said that the three "resolutions" of the UN Committee on Human Rights and the recent adoption of one more "resolution" arouses the suspicion that the UN is being reduced to a tool for implementing the U.S.-sponsored unilateral "policy on human rights issue in the north." The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our hope that the UN will reflect on its approach towards the human rights issue in north Korea, the stand based on criticism and pressure, and opt for a just settlement of it on the basis of sincerity and good faith. We also urge the south Korean government to comprehensively reexamine its passive and defensive stand on which it has only emphasized the peculiarity of the south-north relations and give spurs to creating an international environment.
 Meanwhile, an editor of Minjok Thongsin, made public a commentary titled "No human rights without sovereignty" on Nov. 19 at which he denounced those forces for hailing the adoption of the "resolution". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He observed that they seemed not to know properly about some members of the international community which unconditionally said "yes" to what was sponsored by the U.S., Britain and other powers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These forces are no more than imbeciles who do not know even the fact that the U.S., Britain and other powers are the countries which deprived other countries of their sovereignty and colonized them and have preached human rights and democracy for their peoples and international community, the commentary noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is more deplorable is the fact that some media in south Korea whose position is no better than that under a colonial rule are talking about "human rights issue" in the north and treacherous political forces such as the "Grand National Party" accused the government for people, which abstained from voting for the "resolution," of being a leftist. Such traitorous and sycophantic forces do not understand the stark fact that they will also die when a war breaks out on the Korean Peninsula and it is none other than the U.S. that abuses human rights, in actuality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the way of protecting human rights and world peace to condemn those countries which have threatened other countries by force and violated their sovereignty and stand against the arbitrary practices of a handful of big powers including the U.S. This is, at the same time, the only way of combating terrorism.

S. Korean Right-Wing Conservative Forces Have No Future
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- The "Grand National Party", a general headquarters of flunkeys and traitors and anti-reunification conservative forces, is desperately working to bring back the era of inter-Korean confrontation and the reactionary offensive of the right-wing conservative forces is escalating. It was against this backdrop that the "National League of New Right", a new organization of the right-wing conservative forces, was knocked into shape recently to group all types of fascist remnants including renegades of the "student movement" and conservative hack writers.
 Rodong Sinmun Friday observes in a signed article: This is no more than a foolish fit of those who have no future. Only destruction awaits those who are engrossed in the treacherous moves, swimming against the trend of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The anti-reunification conservative forces in south Korea are the reactionaries of history as they stand in the way of the people's struggle  to achieve independence and reunification, turning their faces away from the changed times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is still betraying the fellow countrymen, swimming against the trend of the times, not away from the old way of thinking dating back to the era of the Cold War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It adopted flunkeyism towards the U.S. as its policy and is blindly toeing the U.S. policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. military domination over south Korea is a stumbling block lying in the way of achieving its progress and development and intensifying the movement for national reunification. However, the GNP is throwing a higher hurdle in the way of the south Koreans' movement for achieving independence by pursuing such flunkeyism towards the U.S. and toeing its line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The group of traitors is making desperate efforts to stand against the fellow countrymen, while kowtowing and yielding to outside forces.
 With no desperation can the reactionaries stop the advance of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The end of the "civilian government" in south Korea resulted in ousting the conservative forces from power who had been engrossed in flunkeyism towards the U.S. and treachery, staying in power for several decades under the active patronage of the U.S. since its troops' occupation of south Korea. This was the result of the dynamic struggle waged by the south Korean people to put an end to the outdated politics characterized by flunkeyism and anti-reunification acts and bring about a new politics of democracy and independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-reunification conservative forces including the GNP are making desperate efforts to block the advance of progressive and pro-reform forces and bring back by-gone days. However, their fate will not be different from their present miserable one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reactionaries of history can never escape a final doom as they are forsaken by the people.

Kim Il Sung's Immortal Exploits Praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung will always live in the hearts of humankind for his immortal exploits performed for the era and history and the rays of Juche will brightly indicate the way to be followed by them at all times.
 M. Jahangir Khan, leader of Comrade Kim Il Sung Works Study Group of Barisal, Bangladesh, who led the delegation of organizations for the study of the Juche idea of Bangladesh, said this when interviewed by a KCNA reporter at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel before its departure for home.
 He said that it was great honor for the delegation to visit Mangyongdae, the holy place of revolution, where the President, founder of the Juche idea and great saint of humankind, was born and spent his childhood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President liberated Korea and devoted his whole life to the happiness of the people and the struggle to accomplish the human cause of independence, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Juche idea is the man-centered idea clarifying that popular masses are the maker of history on the basis of the philosophical principle that man is the master of everything and decides everything. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I became an ardent adherent to the Juche idea, enchanted by his great idea in the course of reading famous works of the President.
 The Juche idea is now being developed and enriched by leader  Kim Jong Il, he stressed.

2nd Video Reunions of Separated Families and Relatives Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- The second video reunions of separated families and relatives were held here on Thursday and Friday.
 When the video reunions started, the families and relatives who have lived separated in the north and the south tried to recall their faces before separation. Upon recognizing each other, they asked how they were and exchanged long pent-up inmost thoughts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those from the north were proud to tell their kin from the south about the independent and creative life they have led to the full under the benevolent care of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also told them that not only themselves but their families are devoting all their wisdom and energies to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation under the benevolent socialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rejoiced at the reunions, they showed photographs of their families and relatives each other and exchanged conversations about their life course.

Subsidiary Health Foodstuff Win Top Prizes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- Kumsamsu, Chongjiryong, Chongsinjong, Singijong, Chonghyolsodangjong, Poganjong and Unicolon made by the Korea Sogyong General Trading Corporation were highly appreciated as subsidiary foodstuffs good for health at the 2005 Northeast Asia Hi-tech Fair. They have efficacious medicinal ingredients to promote health.
 The top prizes were awarded to the foodstuffs at the China International Patent Fair held in Dalian in August. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are made from various precious natural medicinal herbs growing in highland of the country and efficacious ingredients extracted from rare metals by the traditional pharmacy of Koryo medicines with the help of latest technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kumsamsu is a non-toxic and ideal natural anti-cancer agent, which improves the immunity of the human body and represses the proliferation of cancer cell. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chongsinjong relieves the pain in the joints and muscles and neuralgia and helps recover from fatigue. It, thus, is a health food for the alpinists and the aged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unicolon is very efficacious for treating autonomic nervous system disorder and the functional disorder of internal organs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The other subsidiary foodstuffs are potent for the improvement of the microcirculation and portal circulation of the liver and for the prevention and treatment of the diseases such as hyperlipemia, lipotrophy, diabetes and cerebral apoplexy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foodstuffs  are popular in different countries of Asia and Europe.

New Books on Natural Products and Cultural Heritage Off Press
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- The Korean Cultural Preservation Agency has recently published the book "Illustrated Guide to Korean Natural Products" (Vol. 1).
 The book consists of five volumes, which introduce plant, animal, geographical and geological natural products of Korea.
 Printed in the volume one  is a picture of President Kim Il Sung appreciating the natural products in the front of the Koryo Songgyungwan in May, Juche 81 (1992). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book, which deals with flora natural products, gives species of gingko trees and needle-leaf trees according to the order of independent, colony and forest trees and to the order of their ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It inscribes the name of each species of plant in five languages and gives photo-illustrated general feature of the species and photo-accompanied explanation to each national product. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Given in the book are the lists of natural products in provinces, cities and counties and their regional distribution chart. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, different books on cultural heritages of Korea have been published. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book "Common Knowledge on Cultural Heritages" (vol. 1) deals with relics and remains including the three tombs in Kangso, Komunmoru remains and metallic type, national classics, legends and anecdotes including the Kumo myth, Koryo history and true records of the Ri Dynasty.
 The book "History and Culture of Mt. Jongbang" introduces nature, origin of the name, history, geography, relics, remains and legends of the mountain and old poems and folk songs on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is a book titled "Pagodas of Our Country in Middle Ages". It introduces in detail pagoda construction and reason, position of pagoda in temple arrangement, forms and changes of pagodas, sculptures and ornaments, pagoda erection in each age and the position of the pagodas built in Korea in the middle ages in the cultural history.

Greetings Exchanged between DPRK and Angolan Foreign Ministers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 25 (KCNA) -- DPRK Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun exchanged messages of greetings with Angolan Foreign Minister Joao Bernardo De Miranda on the occasion of the 30th anniversary of the independence of Angola and the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries.
 Paek in his message noted that over the last three decades the Angolan people have achieved big successes in their efforts to consolidate the independence of the country and achieve national unity and economic reconstruction and the two countries have had bilateral cooperation and taken joint steps in the international arena in the idea of independence, peace and friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed the belief that the good friendly and cooperative relations existing between the two countries would grow stronger in the fundamental interests of the two peoples and wished the Angolan foreign minister bigger success in his responsible work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Angolan foreign minister in his message said that the Angolan people could consolidate the independence of the country, defend its peace and achieve the prosperity of the country thanks to the support and cooperation rendered by the DPRK for the past 30 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in the message expressed conviction that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would grow stronger and wished the DPRK foreign minister good health and success in his work.
